	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64320375"><p>Too much granularity in insurance data defeats the purpose of insurance pools: That is to spread the risk among a group such that a harm to one is borne by the whole without hardship.</p><p>Actuarial tables already provide risk analysis for groups, individualizing beyond that is counterproductive.</p></div>
